    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The process of detaching a fresco painting from the wall by removing the pigment layer and a layer of intonaco. Cloth is glued to the painted surface and, when dry, the cloth, painting, and plaster are stripped from the wall.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000014911/Frescoes from Florence (1969)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Proceso de desprender una pintura al fresco del muro separando la capa pigmentada y una capa del revoque. Se pega una tela a la superficie pintada y, al secarse, la tela, pintura y yeso son arrancados del muro.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Procedé voor het verwijderen van een frescoschildering van de muur door de pigmentlaag en een intonacolaag te verwijderen. Doek wordt vastgelijmd op het geschilderde oppervlak en wanneer het droog is worden doek, schildering en bepleistering van de muur gehaald.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>藉由移除顏料層與壁畫石灰表層（intonaco），將濕壁畫由牆壁上移除的過程。布料被黏在上了油彩的表面之上，當表面乾燥的時候，布料、繪畫，以及石膏層就會從牆壁上剝除下來。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
